title: For Sale:  NIB Les Baer UTC 1911
postcontent:
Selling my NIB Les Baer Ultimate Tactical Carry model.  I purchased this gun new from Kames in Canton a year ago and it has been sitting unfired in my safe since then.  I'm selling it to fund a different Baer model.

As I said, this is the 5 inch Ultimate Tactical Carry model.  It has the fixed night sights, single sided safety and the thin Cocobolo grips.  The sharp edges have also been nicely blended which I find to be both functional and good looking.  This gun also has the blued finish.  Les Baer builds an incredible 1911, but their blue finish seems to be hit or miss at times.  I can honestly say that the finish on this gun is perfect.  I see a lot of Baers with different shades of finish on the frame and slide when they are new, but the bluing on this gun matches perfectly.  No scrapes or scratches anywhere, as you would expect from a new gun.

The frame to slide fit is perfect, and the lockup is tight as a drum.  Anyone familiar with Les Baer 1911s knows how tight some of them can be, and this one is no exception.  As with most of the semi-custom manufacturers, Baer recommends a 500 round break-in period for each of their guns, after which they smooth out considerably.  Whoever buys this 1911 will have the pleasure of getting to know the gun during the break-in, as you will be the first to fire it outside of the factory.

I have many close-up high resolution pictures uploaded to my Photobucket page.  Unfortunately, Armslist does not allow clickable links in their ads, and some people have still not figured out how to copy and paste, so send me an email and I will answer any questions you have as well as send you the link to the pictures.  It's very rare to find a high-end 1911 on Armslist that is not for sale by a dealer, so get it while you can and skip the taxes.  Buyer must be over 21 years old, have a valid Ohio drivers license and be able to legally own a firearm in the state of Ohio.  CCW holders are preferred but not required.  If more than one person responds to the ad, I will give priority to anyone with a CCW.  Thanks for looking.

Just a feeler...00 Jeep cherokee 4.0 just slightly modified haha. Looking to sell.

Its not 100% finished, but I used to drive it 40+ miles a day to work on the highway until we had twins and gas prices hit the wallet hard. Still runs and drives, starts every time hot or cold. Perfect for summer since all the doors are easily removed.

Full traction 6.5" Long arm lift with 6" stretch leafs in the rear
Balanced 38" swampers with spare
Stroked I6 4.0 with k&n and ac delete,
aux tranny cooler,
optima yellow top battery
New parts everywhere...radiator, motor mounts, fuel pump, starter, brake booster and more
Hydro assist steering with 1ton links and 3/4" rod ends
Detroit locker up front with new warn hubs, bearings, and seals
PIAA fog lights with procomp spotlights for headlights in a yj front clip
Oversized brakes
Remote res fox shocks up front
Procomp adjustable shocks in the rear
Dana 44 hp front with welded tubes
Dana 60 ff rear with welded tubes
Raised gas tank for clearance
I'm sure I'm forgetting some stuff.

The bad part is I haven't gotten around to installing the rear gears. I have the gears and install kit brand new in the box G2 performance gears. 
There are a few small leaks, but it's only the silicone gasket material...I installed the tranny pan after a fluid and filter service when it was 10° out so the silicone didn't form properly....same with the diff covers, very minor but mentionable.
One rear wheel is slightly bent so at high speeds you can feel the shake. $150 for a new wheel from what I've found.
Also the fuel gauge doesn't always work. 

Other than that it's a monster and gets a lot of attention. My loss your gain, with a little more effort you could have a seriously solid trail rig/rock crawler.
